HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 970
By Freeman
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend the Hillsboro High
School boys' lacrosse team upon winning the
2025 TSSAA Class A state championship.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
student athletes who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as true
champions of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such exemplary group of young men is the Hillsboro High School boys'
lacrosse team, whose members have proven themselves to be fierce competitors and truly
worthy of admiration by winning the 2025 TSSAA Class A state championship; and
WHEREAS, competing in the inaugural TSSAA boys' lacrosse season, the Hillsboro
High School Burros rose to the occasion and claimed a hard-fought 12-11 victory over Signal
Mountain High School in the championship game; and
WHEREAS, the Burros held a commanding 9-3 lead before Signal Mountain rallied to
cut the deficit to one goal, but Hillsboro demonstrated resilience and composure in the closing
minutes to secure the title; and
WHEREAS, Spencer Hart led the Burros with four goals in the championship contest,
while Matthew Beller added three goals and two assists to propel Hillsboro High School to
victory; and
WHEREAS, senior midfielder Charlie Schultz provided leadership and determination as
the team withstood the late-game rally, drawing on past championship experience to help
steady the Burros in a tense finish; and
WHEREAS, the following young men proudly displayed the resilience and determination
of the Hillsboro High School Burros: Matthew Beller, Simmons Verner, Joshua Kuehn, Joseph
Bryant, Spencer Hart, Clayton Bulbulkaya, Walter Harris, Christopher Conk, Seamus Havron,
HJR0970
013552
- 1 -

Lucian Bahan, Finn Casella, Baker Hasty, Ian Dukes, Paxton Griffith, Soren Svenson, Corrian
Phillips, Ethan Biniaz, Tate Johnson, Adler Hatcher, Richard Demers, James Henning, Sims Hill
III, Ethan Winston, and Rowan Cass; and
WHEREAS, Hillsboro High School's superb performance would not have been possible
without the expert guidance of Head Coach Cody Moore and Assistant Coach Jackson Nash
Bolton and the unfailing support of the players' families, their fans, and their community; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Hillsboro High School boys' lacrosse team epitomize all
that is good in today's student athletes, as they have achieved a premier level of success in
competition while exhibiting perseverance, teamwork, and the highest degree of character; and
WHEREAS, the perseverance, determination, work ethic, and talent of this group of
young men not only made possible a championship but also surely bode well for their future
success; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud the Hillsboro High
School Burros for their outstanding season on the field; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend the members of the Hillsboro High School boys'
lacrosse team upon winning the 2025 TSSAA Class A state championship and extend to them
our best wishes for every continued success in all their future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
